In conclusion, we demonstrated sky-blue PeLED with EQE of
11% and blue PeLED with EQE of 4.8%, by overcoming the
limitation from the low PLQE of wide-bandgap perovskites. The
combination of layered perovskite formation and YCl
poration enhances the PLQE from 1.1% to 49.7%, which also
enhance the material stability by suppressing ion migration. This
study reveals that the low PLQE in most Cl:Br-based perovskites
ﬁlms limits the LED efﬁciency. Further research to improve the
PLQE of wide-bandgap perovskite ﬁlms to 100% should increase
the EQE of sky-blue-emission PeLEDs to over 20%.
